The paper focuses on developing a supervised algorithm for symbolic music style transfer, which involves generating aligned data using a synthetic data generation scheme. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). Additionally, the paper uses deep learning-based algorithms for style transfer, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves developing a model for translating music accompaniments between different styles, which could be categorized under cs.SI (Sound and Image Processing). Finally, the paper deals with symbolic music, which is a sub-field of music information retrieval, and could be classified under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
